64
00:03:14,569 --> 00:03:17,000
How would they see the conflict?

65
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,620
Try to get out of your
own myopic point of view

66
00:03:19,620 --> 00:03:22,680
and see how you're
contributing to that conflict.

67
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:24,590
Sometimes it's a very
powerful realization

68
00:03:24,590 --> 00:03:27,080
that you'll make about
how you're contributing

69
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:29,330
to this conflict, and
that might give you

70
00:03:29,330 --> 00:03:32,430
an idea of what the
pathway is for resolution.

71
00:03:32,430 --> 00:03:36,050
So this topic's really
been about that idea

72
00:03:36,050 --> 00:03:38,330
of shifting your
perspective, seeing

73
00:03:38,330 --> 00:03:39,880
the world through others' eyes.

74
00:03:39,879 --> 00:03:42,430
It's not always an easy
